          <link xlink:href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26758199"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>Dual oxidase 1 [1]. 
DUOX1 generates hydrogen peroxide which is required for the activity of thyroid peroxidase/TPO and lactoperoxidase/LPO [1]. 

STAT6 did interacts specifically with DC-specific genes like DUOX1 and SLAMF1 in DC differentiation [2].

Using matrix-scan, we predicted binding sites for IRF4, and Pu.1 in the regulatory region, annotated with chromHMM in this study, of the DUOX1 coding gene.</comment>
      </annotation>
