      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q13291"/>
          <link xlink:href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26758199"/>
          <link xlink:href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29284783/"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>Signaling lymphocytic activation molecule [1]. 
SLAM receptors triggered by homo- or heterotypic cell-cell interactions are modulating the activation and differentiation of a wide variety of immune cells and are involved in the regulation and interconnection of both innate and adaptive immune response [1]. 
STAT6 did interacts specifically with DC-specific genes like DUOX1 and SLAMF1 in DC differentiation [2]. Number of TFs such as IRF4, STAT6, could bind to SLAMF1 promoter and regulate its activity [3].
Using matrix-scan, we predicted binding sites for IRF4, and ELK4, in the regulatory region, annotated with chromHMM in this study, of the SLAMF1 coding gene.</comment>
      </annotation>
