          <link xlink:href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29262348"/>
          <link xlink:href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22323450/"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DRB1 beta chain [1], expressed by DCs [2,3]
STAT5 promotes the expression of MHC class II transactivatorprotein (CIITA), which is essential for proper transcripiton of the MHC class II promoter [4].
</comment>
