          <link xlink:href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22328945"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>C-C motif chemokine 2  [1]. 
CCL2 is a chemokine constitutively produced by immature MDDCs, acting as a ligand for C-C chemokine receptor CCR2 [1].
The CCL2 chemokine directs monocyte/macrophage recruitmentinto tissues under resting and inflamed conditions [2].
ERK upregulated CCL2 expression while impairing the expression of DC maturation markers (RUNX3, ITGB7, IDO1) [3]. 
Using matrix-scan, we predicted binding sites for FOXO1, STAT3, and STAT5 in the regulatory region, annotated with chromHMM in this study, of the CCL2 gene.

</comment>
      </annotation>
