          <link xlink:href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29262348"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>C-C motif chemokine 22 [1], moDC marker [2]. 
May play a role in the trafficking of activated/effector T-lymphocytes to inflammatory sites and other aspects of activated T-lymphocyte physiology. Chemotactic for monocytes, dendritic cells and natural killer cells [1].

Using Matrix-scan , we predicted binding sites for AHR, NCOR2, FOXO1, KLF4, and MAFB in the regulatory region, annotated with chromHMM in this study, of the CCL22 gene.</comment>
