        <comment>Toll-like receptor 3 [1], moDC marker[2].
TLRs control host immune response against pathogens through recognition of molecular patterns specific to microorganisms [1].
Using matrix-scan, we predicted binding sites for IRF4, and PRDM1, in the regulatory region, annotated with chromHMM in this study, of the TLR3 coding gene.
