        </linklist>
        <comment>Toll-like receptor 8 [1], moDC marker [2].
Endosomal receptor that plays a key role in innate and adaptive immunity. 
It controls host immune response against pathogens through recognition of RNA degradation products specific to microorganisms that are initially processed by RNASET2 [3]
Using matrix-scan, we predicted binding sites for CEBPA, KLF4, and STAT6 in the regulatory region, annotated with chromHMM in this study, of TLR8 coding gene.</comment>
