          <link xlink:href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31331973/"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>Tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily member 5 [1], moDC marker [2].
Receptor for TNFSF5/CD40LG [3]. 
CD40 transduces TRAF6- and MAP3K8-mediated signals that activate ERK in macrophages and B cells, leading to induction of immunoglobulin secretion [1].

Using matrix-scan, we predicted binding sites for AP1 in the regulatory region, annotated with chromHMM in this study, of the CD40 coding gene.

</comment>
      </annotation>
