          <link xlink:href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29262348"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>T-lymphocyte activation antigen CD86 [1], moDC marker [2,3]. 
Receptor involved in the costimulatory signal essential for T-lymphocyte proliferation and interleukin-2 production, by binding CD28 or CTLA-4. 
CD86 may play a critical role in the early events of T-cell activation and costimulation of naive T-cells [1].

Using matrix-scan, we predicted binding sites for AP1 in the regulatory region, annotated with chromHMM in this study, of the CD86 coding gene.</comment>
      </annotation>
