          <link xlink:href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26758199/"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>CD83 antigen [1], moDC marker [2,3]. May play a significant role in antigen presentation or the cellular interactions that follow lymphocyte activation [1].

Using matrix-scan, we predicted binding sites for IRF4, NFKB2, and STAT6 in the regulatory region, annotated with chromHMM in this study, of the CD83 gene.
</comment>
      </annotation>
