          <link xlink:href="https://www.genecards.org/cgi-bin/carddisp.pl?gene=THBD&amp;keywords=CD141"/>
          <link xlink:href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29448070"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>Thrombomodulin [1,2], marker for moDC [3].
CD141 is a specific endothelial cell receptor that forms a 1:1 stoichiometric complex with thrombin. This complex is responsible for the conversion of protein C to the activated protein Ca [1]. 
Using matrix-scan, we predicted binding sites for ATF1, CEBPa, CREB1, IRF4, and USF1 in the regulatory region, annotated with chromHMM in this study, of the CD141 gene.

</comment>
      </annotation>
