        </linklist>
        <comment>Lymphocyte antigen 75 [1], moDC marker [2]. 
Acts as an endocytic receptor to direct captured antigens from the extracellular space to a specialized antigen-processing compartment (By similarity). Causes reduced proliferation of B-lymphocytes [1].

Using matrix-scan, we predicted binding sites for FOXO1, AP1, and PRDM1 in the regulatory region, annotated with chromHMM in this study, of the DEC205 gene.
</comment>
