    <annotation>
      <linklist>
        <link xlink:href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/8145033"/>
        <link xlink:href="http://rsat.eu"/>
        <link xlink:href="http://jaspar.genereg.net/"/>
      </linklist>
      <comment>Sallusto and Lazavecchia (1994) describe for the first time a protocol enabling the differentiate human monocytes into dendritic cells (moDC)  in vitro, in the presence of granulocyte macrophage colony stimulating factor (CSF2) and interleukin 4 (IL4) [1].
This model integrates current data on the signaling pathways involved in this differentiation process, together with relevant transcription factor ChIP-seq data
In particular, we consider novel putative regulatory interactions based on the analysis of target gene promoters, using the tool matrix-scan from the RSAT software suite [2] and selected  transcriptional factor binding profiles from the JASPAR database [3]</comment>
    </annotation>
